med the company by accelerating a divestiture and costcutting plan strengthening profitable existing lines of business and aggressively seeking new business in  blau renamed isc as griffon corporation a name inspired by the mythical halfeagle halflion symbolizing the combined strengths of the companys different subsidiaries blau retired as ceo in march  and was succeeded by ron kramer who had married blaus daughter stephanie in  kramer had served on the companys board of directors since  and was elected vice chairman in  in addition to his role at griffon blau served as chairman of the board and ceo of aeroflex incorporated a manufacturer of electronic components and test equipment from  to  and as mayor deputy mayor and trustee of the village of old westbury new york in  blau and his wife received the theodore roosevelt award at the legal aid societys annual servant of justice awards dinner referencesedit  a b executive profile harvey r blau bloomberg business retrieved  october    company overview of blau kramer wactlar  lieberman pc bloomberg business retrieved  october    a b c rd annual servant of justice awards dinner program pdf legal aid society  retrieved  october    miss arlene j garrett bride of harvey blau new york times march   retrieved  october    rabb charles may   unhappy shareholders torpedo loans newsday p  retrieved  october    edward garrett  chairman of instrument systems corp new york times march   retrieved  october    griffon corporation international directory of company histories   retrieved  october    a b c board members griffon corp retrieved  october    incantalupo tom july   jericho firm escapes financial hole newsday p  retrieved  october    doors diapers and defense griffon corp switches name shifts directions newsday march     stephanie blau has wedding new york times april   retrieved  october    bernstein james march   griffon gets new credit line ceo newsday pp a retrieved  october    griffon corporation names ronald j kramer ch